HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 42
By Marsh
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Dan Long on the
occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Dan Long of Lincoln County is one such estimable person, who evinces the
greatest integrity and probity in all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, having served with distinction for twenty-two years on the Lincoln County
Election Commission, Mr. Long is taking his well-deserved retirement from that august body;
and
WHEREAS, he began his esteemed tenure with the Lincoln County Election
Commission as a poll official and later became a voting machine technician; his involvement
continued to grow and evolve over the years, with him ultimately serving as chairman of the
commission; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Long's devotion to State election laws has undoubtedly contributed to
the faithful execution of countless Lincoln County elections over the years and to the
commission's status as an exemplar for others across the Volunteer State; and
WHEREAS, always ahead of the curve with regard to ever-evolving technology, Dan
Long was a mentor to new members and a true leader within the Lincoln County Election
County Commission, earning the respect of his colleagues across all parties and perspectives;
and
WHEREAS, a native and lifelong resident of Waynesboro, Dan Long graduated from
Waynesboro High School and thereafter went to work at Western Electric from 1961 to 1997,
retiring after thirty-six years of astute service; and
