WHEREAS, after his retirement from Western Electric, he began building his family
home in Lincoln County; the substantial project began in 1998, and his family moved into the
home in 2001; and
WHEREAS, he has also served his community as a member of the Fayetteville Elks
Lodge, of which he is a past Exalted Ruler; and
WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, Mr. Long has been blessed with the
love and support of his wife of fifty-eight years, Barbara Snow Long; daughters, Suzanne and
Dane; three grandchildren; and three great-grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, Dan Long exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community that
are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Long is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service that
have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend Dan Long for his honorable and astute service to the good
people of Tennessee throughout his twenty-two-year tenure with the Lincoln County Election
Commission and extend to him our heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement and
every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
